From the very first Mannheim Steamroller Christmas album (recorded more than 20 years ago) and featuring their signature funky rock style, here is the good king effectively adapted for concert band by Robert Longfield. Your horn section is sure to have fun with this one, as will the percussion section. A great way to shake up your holiday concert! (Grade 3)

Heralded by a fanfare-like figure for trumpets in the first strain, here is an appealing German-style march solidly scored for young players. Low brass take the lead on the second strain, followed by a contrasting lyrical sectionfeaturing the woodwinds. The full ensemble brings us to a rousing finish in this terrific-sounding march. (This is a nice follow-up to Johnnie's earlier international marches St. Petersburg

Though Silent Night has been arranged for band many times before, this unique setting by Rick Kirby deserves special attention. An oboe solo (cued for alto sax) accompanied by piano sets the stage for an impressive rhapsodicapproach that includes lush full ensemble passages with harmonic twists, solos for recorder (flute), bassoon (tenor sax) and euphonium. Rick's beautiful rendering ends with the band singing Silent
titre: A Winter's Night (based on Silent Night)

description: You can sense right from the start that someone is sneaking around to give that unexpected surprise to a friend or foe! The percussion provide a simple but effective groove, and a jazzy middle section helps to mix things up andoffers nice variety. Written in a single tempo throughout, here is an entertaining piece that will be a blast to perform, and yet musically rewarding to teach. Dur: 2:45

The lush harmonies in this lyrical and emotional piece will provide your students with a wonderful learning tool to improve listening skills, while at the same time providing a spellbinding effect for the listener. Featuring ablend of soft textures, full ensemble peaks, a brief solo flute cadenza, and a sensitive orchestration throughout, the music effectively alludes to far off places. Dur: 3:50

The final movement of Percy Grainger's masterwork  Lincolnshire Posy  is arranged here for younger bands with reduced instrumentation. Similar to his earlier adaptation of “Horkstow Grange”, Michael Sweeney carefully maintains the structural and harmonic integrity of the original while providing an authentic-sounding version at an easy level. Certain to become a “must have” for the
titre: The Lost Lady Found (from Lincolnshire Posy)

description: Perfect as a concert opener, this energetic piece uses a pulsating rhythmic pattern to build intensity, along with strong melodic fragments passed around the entire band. A brief contrasting middle theme in minor sets up thedramatically faster and exciting final strain. Dur: 2:35

This intense and emotional work was commissioned by the Indiana Music Educators Association and was premiered at the 2011 IMEA Convention with the composer conducting. Written as a gift to longtime friend of music education, Dr.Tim Lautzenheiser, the piece is basically lyrical in nature with beautiful lines and colors. A brief faster section, in the words of the composer, “describes that uncomfortable time when

The Native American Cree tribe refer to the aurora borealis (or northern lights) as the dance of the spirits. Using a variety of unusual sounds and effects, quickly changing textures and surprises, Michael Sweeney has created amusical impression of this phenomenon's stunning beauty and unpredictable nature. An exciting and unique addition to the young band repertoire, this will be enjoyable to rehearse and perform.

Inspired by the musical tradition of early American folk songs, Johnnie Vinson has composed this appealing suite of three contrasting dance styles. The movements include Tar Heel Two-Step, Woodland Waltz, and Blue Ridge Reel. Sureto be an entertaining and rewarding work for young bands. (Grade 2.5) Dur: 5:15

The stunning artwork of Georgia O'Keeffe is no more apparent than in her famous 1921 painting entitled Blue and Green Music. Fittingly commissioned by the Patrick Marsh Middle School in Sun Prairie, Wisconsin (O'Keeffe'sbirthplace), Samuel Hazo does an amazing job of portraying subtle as well as bold colors into musical terms. Based on a single theme that is manipulated and varied throughout, the piece progresses
sous_titre: Based on the Georgia O'Keeffe painting Blue and Green Music

description: Composed in the style of a Cajun two-step, the simple melody is stated first by the trumpets with a zydeco-inspired accompaniment. An optional advanced trombone part is included with New Orleans style tailgate effects. A washboardand optional keyboard bass part will add to the festive, homegrown sound of a traditional Cajun band in this unique piece that is easy and fun to play! Dur: 2:15

In this dynamic multi-style overture for band, Michael Sweeney opens with stark percussive hits, brass fanfares, and swirling woodwind effects. A fast tempo and long build follows, using non-traditional harmonies and overlappinglayers of sound, climaxing with a majestic, soaring statement by the entire ensemble. The slower middle section features a solo flute accompanied by rich sonorities and counterlines. The fast

This exciting, innovative new work from Robert Buckley was commissioned by the Troy University Symphony Band in honor of the 37th annual Southeastern United States Concert Band Clinic in Alabama. Using a recurring two-measureloop, this uniquely constructed piece is built up around various musical building blocks that are constantly evolving and transforming. The music is dramatic and dynamic, with full-blown ensemble

A tour de force of exotic sounds and emotional design, this major work from Samuel Hazo will leave your audiences breathless. Based on the hauntingly beautiful Sunayama, this composition tells a story of the inner conflict of a Japanese girl who falls in love with an American. She is torn between a life with him in America and her longing for the culture of her childhood. From time to time she plays a music box given
titre: Fantasy On A Japanese Folk Song

description: A new generation of musicals is hitting the Great White Way, resulting in a renewed vitality in the music written for the stage. Here is a dynamic collection of future classics in a sparkling and entertaining medley from Michael Brown. Includes: “Springtime for Hitler”  (The Producers),  “The Avenue Q Theme,” “Always Look on the Bright Side of Life”  (Spamalot),

In the latest installment of Indiana Jones blockbuster movies, John Williams has created yet another memorable soundtrack. In speaking about the experience of composing for these exciting films, he says it has consistently offeredme a wild and joyous ride. This accurately describes The Adventures of Mutt with its relentless energy and spirit of fun. Performance time - ca. 3:10
Solidly scored for beginning bands, here is a driving, upbeat arrangement of Adele's Song of the Year hit.

La musique de James Newton Howard saisit ingénieusement l’atmosphère et le drame du film Hunger Games. Dans cette adaptation remarquable pour orchestre, Jay Bocook met en valeur les grands moments de la musique, y compris une interprétation particulière du cri obsédant des geais moqueurs.

100 years after the sinking of the Titanic, we are still drawn in and touched by this tragic story. Reported as one of the last songs played by the music ensemble aboard the ship, this tender hymn capsulizes the emotions of the event. Beautifully scored by Michael Brown for young bands.
From the movie soundtrack for The Hunger Games, here is a great-sounding arrangement of the hit song Safe & Sound recorded by Taylor Swift featuring The Civil Wars.

Splashes of color and striking textures combine with an underlying street beat driving pulse in this joyous overture for band. Throughout, Michael skillfully manipulates melodic and rhythmic fragments as they are developed andpassed from section to section. A brief slow section and tender chorale provide a poignant calm before the celebration of rhythm and dance returns for the uplifting conclusion. A rewarding piece

Here is an exciting and powerful work for very young players with one year of experience. Written using a single tempo throughout, a driving 8th note pulse and minor mode provide the underlying energy as the melody is passedaround to different sections of the band. With no syncopation and repetitive patterns, your band will sound great with limited rehearsal time. Dur: 2:20

Composed to give young players the opportunity to experience mixed meter in a controlled setting (in this case, 3/4 + 4/4), Incandescence uses an engaging and energetic rhythmic groove to make this big step fun and enjoyable. Inaddition to being a perfect vehicle for teaching and internalizing a constant 8th- note subdivision, this piece will be exciting and rewarding to perform. Dur: 2:10

Composed in 12/8 and entirely in one energetic tempo, this masterful work is a musical tribute to the late Sir Malcolm Arnold, one of the most notable English composers of our time. The opening section features a variety of shortsolo statements of the theme, which then leads to well-timed and impressive declarations from the entire ensemble. Within in the confines of this brief yet impressive work, Richard manages to

From Rimsky-Korsalov's opera Snow Maiden, Dance of the Tumblers is considered to be one of this composer's most well known themes. Although brief in duration, this vibrant and energetic dance contains a wealth of music, and with its light-hearted spirit, is a perfect teaching tool for young players. Dur: 1:35
titre: Dance of the Tumblers (from The Snow Maiden)

description: This easy yet exciting composition for young players captures the energy and forward motion of a whirlwind. James Curnow creates musical diversity through melodic development and rhythmic contrast, plus a brief bit of calm beforethe frantic pace and windstorm returns. Sure to be an engaging work for your band.

Inspired by the mountains of West Virginia, Valley Mist portrays a beautiful scene of cloud-like mist as it flows gently around the hills encompassing the entire valley in an atmosphere of peace and tranquility. Quoting theAppalachian folk song Down in the Valley, this sensitively scored work includes an optional gentle rain effect with the use of finger snaps. Sure to be an enjoyable change of pace for any program.

On a Sunday afternoon in May of 2011 tornados devastated the city of Joplin, Missouri. In Perfect Silence, I Often Gaze at the New Stars is intended as a musical tribute to those who lost their lives that day and to those heroeswho gave everything they could to help others. The music is a beautiful blending of sounds and moods, and carries with it a full range of emotions from reflective quiet moments to the massive
titre: In Perfect Silence, I Often Gaze at the New Stars

description: John Barnes Chance composed his landmark work for band, Incantation and Dance, in 1960 while in residence at the high school in Greensboro, North Carolina. Commissioned by the Union County (NC) Honor Band, Prelude and Pursuit paystribute to this important composition and its North Carolina connection. A haunting chant-like theme played by the clarinets sets the tone for the slow section. Similar to Chance's work, the

Written entirely in 5/4, this captivating and rhythmically dynamic work explores a variety of moods and styles within this single meter. After the initial fanfare, the piece winds through creative textures and hypnotic patternsuntil reaching a glorious full ensemble climatic section. Providing interesting and important roles for every section (particularly percussion) this will be a joy to prepare and perform. Dur:

Featuring a flowing lyric style and beautiful harmonies, this composition for beginning groups allows you to teach phrasing and musicality in a rewarding setting. With easy rhythms and moderate ranges, this is very attainable foryoung players. Dur: 2:30 (Grade 1-1/2)

The term dark horse originated in horse racing describing an unknown entry, but also carries the connotation of an underdog in politics or sports. Composed in 6/8 and using a single brisk tempo throughout, Night of the Dark Horse is an energetic musical journey dedicated to the efforts of unlikely winners everywhere. Dur: 2:40

Undercurrents provides an electrifying, virtuosic showcase for the whole ensemble - featuring a series of solos, duets and trios, as well as highlighting the various chamber sections within the band. The music was inspired by watching schools of fish and flocks of birds perpetually moving with the ocean currents and air currents. Every once in a while a single solo shape will appear - or two or three - they dance

LOL (Laugh Out Loud)  is a wacky, fast-and-furious barn-burner reminiscent of a circus march or “screamer.” It was written for the Naden Band of the Royal Canadian Navy in celebration of their 75th anniversary andas an opportunity to display their dazzling technical facility and humor. Cartoon-like Trombone glissandi, flying woodwinds, dizzying brass and laughing rhythms create a zany and thrilling off the wall
First appearing in the 1980 film Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back, this sinister and dramatic march has become one of the best known movie themes of all time. Performance time - ca. 3:00
sous_titre: From STAR WARS: Episode V - The Empire Strikes Back

description: This descriptive and engaging work follows the ancient tale of a handsome young prince forced (through evil sorcery) to live part of his life as a dragon. He marries the beautiful Griselda under the condition she never try to uncover his dark secret. Fate and curiosity intervene and she discovers his scaly and hideous identity only to be banished from his kingdom forever. With a significant portion of the fast

Walking to the Sky takes an epic, cinematic approach to celebrate humankind's collective quest for wisdom and transcendence. It was inspired by a 100-foot Jonathan Borofsky sculpture, which creates the illusion of a group ofpeople walking skyward into infinity. With pulsing percussion, heroic brass, haunting melodies, sudden shifts in dynamics and dramatic key changes, everyone in the ensemble gets a chance to star
Movement I from Everything Beautiful (HL04004296).

Composed in the 1700s, this traditional Irish ballad was a lament of homesickness by its author, and is now a tender and beloved melody appearing on countless recordings. Also known as The Wind from the South or An Gaoth Aneas,this setting for second year players provides melody for all sections of the band along with subtle and tasteful harmonic variants. Dur: 2:35

Inspired by the Arikara (uh-RIK-a-RAH) tribe of Native Americans based in North Dakota, this work by James Meredith is an evocative piece without portraying any specific event or story. Opening with a plaintive flute solosupported by an exotic percussion backdrop, the piece features a chorale-like statement in the winds before moving to the faster and more rhythmic main section. Mixing early American imagery with

Commissioned for the Madison County (IN) Middle School Honor Band, the title and nature of this work references the Indiana state motto, The Crossroads of America. By contrasting a bold and majestic statement with an invigoratingmixed-meter faster section, Crossroads portrays two divergent musical paths in an appealing and very attainable work for young bands. Dur: 3:50

The Machine Awakes is the sound of something not human (but of humans hands) - something not entirely organic, but most definitely alive - waking up for the first time. From the opening swirling textures, we sense the firsthesitant sparks of thought, attempting to find form and coherence. This new machine comes fully awake, possessed of emphatic self-determination and purpose. The Machine Awakes¦gives ensembles with
titre: The Machine Awakes (for Band Plus Electronics)

description: Here's a very easy novelty number that captures the fun and goofiness of bobblehead dolls. With clever visual and vocal effects, plus some percussion feature spots, this is sure to be enjoyed by players and audience alike. Dur:2:00

Reminiscent of a musical style from the heyday of Broadway musicals,  Johnnie Vinson  has created this lively and entertaining cut time march.   Composed using the traditional march form,  Broadway!  includes interesting lines for all instruments and a nice variety in scoring and dynamics. Dur: 2:30.   Instrumentation: Flute, Oboe, Bassoon, Bb Clarinet 1, Bb Clarinet 2, Bb Clarinet 3, Eb Alto Clarinet, Bb Bass

En 1970 furent diffusés les premiers épisodes de la série télévisée  Colditz . Le compositeur et arrangeur canadien Robert Farnon en écrivit la bande son. La série raconte l’histoire des soldats britanniques retenus prisonniers au Ch teaude Colditz (Allemagne) durant la Seconde Guerre mondiale. L’arrangement réalisé par Philip Sparke apporte élégance et puissance à tout programme de concert !
sous_titre: Theme from the BBC TV Series COLDITZ

description: This lively 6/8 march from John Philip Sousa remains one of his best-known and most performed marches. While keeping the essence of the original intact, Jay Bocook does a masterful job of adjusting the instrumentation and rangesto be playable by just about any young band. An American classic that's perfect for any program! Dur: 2:30 (Grade 3)

The logging industry of Rib Lake in northern Wisconsin faded away 70 years ago, but echoes of that era remain today. Echoes in the Woods depicts the large mechanized logging camps of that earlier time, and also the quiet beauty of the forests and lakes in the region today. Using an overture format and a sense of bold adventure, this work features exciting rhythmic passages contrasted with a flowing and lyrical middle

Using nothing faster than a quarter note (except 8th notes in percussion) and working in melody spots for every section, Michael Oare does a masterful job of capturing a sense of adventure - and possibly danger! - in this powerful work for beginners. This is sure to become a favorite! Dur: 1:55

Composed entirely in a single fast tempo, this distinctive work uses a 2-measure rhythmic pattern as the underlying unifying element. Intensity and pacing are skillfully created using dynamics along with instrument groups added in layers, all culminating in an exciting finish. Featuring some unpredictable twists and turns, this one is fun for all sections of the band!

The Wildcat Creek in central Indiana forms a valley connecting all schools in the Howard County area for whom this piece was written. Opening with the percussion section in a stately style, the main theme is first heard in a chorale-like setting. Designed as an extended fanfare, the piece quickly builds in intensity with each subsequent phrase, and culminates in a fast-paced and brilliant sounding ending flourish.

Celebrating the spirit of hope and determination of the early pioneers on the Iowa plains, this bold and varied overture also pays tribute to the historical importance of railroading to the city of Algona. Using a wide range of styles and timbres, Algona Crossing allows every section of the band a chance to shine. (Note: The piano part is optional and cued in mallets and woodwinds.) Dur: 5:10

La chanteuse pop Adele a célébré un retour succès sur le hit-parade avec ce tube puissant de son album  25 . En alternant les textures plus fines avec des passages tutti pour l’orchestre entier admirablement bien, Johnnie Vinson met cette chanson populaire la disposition de joueurs de deuxième année.

From the classic WWII film from 1957 Bridge on the River Kwai, here is  Malcolm Arnold 's famous march that incorporates Kenneth Alford's Colonel Bogey March along with Arnold's original counterline melody. The whistling part is optional but adds a unique and authentic touch.
Sorti pour la première fois en 1975, ce tube rock est la chanson phare du groupe Kiss et est resté un hymne rock familier. Voici un arrangement ingénieux et énergique pour vos concerts.

Outre son succès sur le hit-parade pop, ce thème entraînant et dynamique de Justin Timberlake se trouve dans le fi lm animé  Les Trolls . Le thème du début commence par un solo pour saxophone alto, puis pour les trombones et barytons, et enfi n pour le reste de l’ensemble. Avec des parties intéressantes pour tous les registres, cet arrangement sera sans doute un succès auprès de votre band ainsi que de votre public.

The race is on! Lightspeed is a high-velocity piece built almost entirely on fast-moving staccato eighth notes. Inspired by the painting technique of pointillism, which uses small distinct dots of color combining to form an image, the overall effect of Lightspeed is an energetic ride that is exciting and fun for the audience as well as the performers. Dur: 2:00

Composée la même année que ses  Danses slaves ,  la Sérénade pour vents  de Dvorák est également dans un style nationaliste qui refl ète les éléments rythmiques et mélodiques de la musique folklorique tchèque. Cette adaptation pour orchestre repose sur le premier mouvement et bénéficie d’une orchestration riche et d’une note martiale solennelle.
titre: Slavonic March (from Serenade for Winds, Op. 44)

description: Written as a celebratory piece, From The Highest Peak is a rousing overture that explodes with energy and is a tribute to the pursuit of excellence and the triumph of the human spirit. With powerful fanfares, triumphant melodies, driving percussion and dynamic contrasts, this exciting concert opener moves through different musical colors without ever losing its relentless drive.Dur: 3:15

Stretching along the North Carolina coast are the barrier islands, ports and beaches collectively known as the Crystal Coast. Rich in history and natural beauty, Michael Oare's impressive-sounding overture for young players paintsa descriptive picture of this wondrous area. Dur: 2:30

The opening movement of Grainger's Lincolnshire Posy is the brief yet engaging Lisbon and has been arranged here for young players and reduced instrumentation. Even with minor simplification and modest ranges, the character andauthenticity shines through in this skilled adaptation. Dur: 1:30

Recorded by the Carpenters in 1970, this tender and familiar tune has remained a consistent holiday favorite through the years, and has been covered by a wide range of artists. This great sounding version for younger players issure to be instantly recognized and appreciated by all.

This entertaining medley of great show music combines Superstar Theme, Don't Cry For Me Argentina, King Herod's Song, and Memory into a moving and dramatic medley that you and your students will love!
titre: Andrew Lloyd Webber A Symphonic Portrait

description: Lowden - Grade 4

Based on the distinctive and mesmerizing version recorded by Mannheim Steamroller, this authentic adaptation by Robert Longfield could be the hit of your holiday concert. Beautifully scored with creative harmonies and band vocals.
Nowak - Grade 4

Over their twenty year span, the Canadian Brass have recorded many memorable Christmas songs that have become classic recordings heard everywhere.  Here are six of their favorites, woven together into an outstanding medley for band.  Includes: Jingle Bells; Good King Wenceslas; Lo, How A Rose E'er Blooming; Carol Of The Bells; Silent Night; and O, Come All Ye Faithful.
Christensen - Grade 4
sous_titre: Love Me Tender - Don't Be Cruel - Heartbreak Hotel - Blue Suede Shoes - Can't Help Falling In Love
titre: Pop and Rock Legends: A Tribute to Elvis

description: Sousa/Brion - Grades 4-5

Includes: All My Lovin', A Hard Day's Night, Ticket To Ride, Yesterday, Norwegian Wood, Got To Get You Into My Life, Here, There and Everywhere, The Fool On The Hill, Penny Lane, Maxwell's Silver Hammer, Lady Madonna, and Something.
titre: Pop and Rock Legends: Music of the Beatles

description: First published in 1964, this dynamic work endures as a classic for young concert bands. Heavily influenced by the modal folk idiom found in early Welch and British band works, this new edition features a full score and is dedicated by the composer to the memory of Dr. Frederick Fennell. Dur: 5:35 (Includes full performance CD)
Includes: It's Beginning To Look A Lot Like Christmas, The Christmas Song, and We Need A Little Christmas.

Completely true to its title, this medley os four favorites is a superb addition to any holiday program!  Beginning with a maestoso introduction, this includes a light rock setting of Rockin' Around The Christmas Tree, a relaxed setting of Rudolph, The Red-Nosed Reindeer, and Holly Jolly Christmas, a warm, rubato treatment of I Heard The Bells On Christmas Day, and a very effective maestoso finale.
Score and parts for Concert Band.

Recorded by South African DJ and record producer Master KG and featuring Nomcebo Zikode this song has become an internet sensation along with the many dance challenges from around the globe. The uplifting melody and infectious rhythmic groove help make this one immediately appealing.

The beautiful composition Benediction has established itself in the repertoire for full concert band. Composer John Stevens has skillfully adapted his work for flexible instrumentation retaining the rich chorale flavor and flowing melodies of the original. Various options are available for the featured solo spots at the beginning and end.
Birdland (Lowden) Concert Band Score/Parts
Classic greats from the Big Band Era! Guaranteed to be a highlight on any program. Includes: String Of Pearls, Satin Doll, Sophisticated Lady, Intermission Riff, and Opus One.

We guaramtee that this is the best example of 'rock & roll' for young band that you'll find anywhere!  The tune, made famous by Bill Haley And The Comets says everything there is to say about early 'rock & roll' and this arrangement by Zane Van Auken is superb!
Nowak - Grade 3
Here's the exciting Spanish classic made popular by Stan Kenton.  This powerful arrangement will add flair and drama to any performance!

With a career spanning 4 decades, Frank Cofield was a key composer/arranger/editor during the formative years of Hal Leonard. His writing was always fresh and his orchestrational style allowed bands of all sizes to sound their best. Frank passed away in 2005. Here is one of his classic arrangements that works just as well today as when it was first published more than 20 years ago.
Nowak - Grade 3

From Andrew Lloyd Webber's powerful opera Evita, here is a marvelous setting of the well-known main song. Written in moderately slow Latin style, this arrangement contains dramatic emotional peaks and a variety of scoring techniques.
Here's a delightful way to begin your holiday performance!
The Herbie Hancock classic in an easy setting for very young bands.  This jazz/rock standard is another great way to teach a new style and motivate young players.

Based on Mozart's keyboard variations on Ah! Vous Dirai-je, Maman, K. 265, the main theme of this arrangement is also known as Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star. The variations are sophisticated yet easy to learn, and every section in the band has a chance to play the melody. Creative and effective writing for beginning players. (2:25)
titre: Variations on a Theme by Mozart

description: Here is an outstanding selection for very young bands written in an uplifting festive style. There is a nice variety in scoring even for this easy level, and very effective use of dynamics. Easy and fun to teach.
Joseph Zawinul's hit chart in an easy and highly imaginative arrangement.
Here's a terrific concert march dedicated to the American aviator, Charles Lindbergh. A perfect choice to open any concert.
This 60's favorite arranged for beginning bands is fun for all!
Everybody's favorite snow man will make a grand appearance at your Winter concert with this sparkling yet easy arrangement. Perfectly scored to sound full with just about any band!

The opening Chorale section of this very appealling beginning band piece introduces the theme that is then used in the Canon that follows. Skillfully designed to pass the melody to every section, this is a very rewarding piece for beginning groups. First published in 1984.

Already a classic in the grade 1 repertoire, Anne McGinty's composition sounds sophisticated without being hard. It features effective use of polychords, modal harmonies and a driving percussion part. Written with just a single tempo, this is sure to make your beginners sound great! Dur: 2:05

The term dark horse originated in horse racing describing an unknown entry, but also carries the connotation of an underdog in politics or sports. Composed in 6/8 and using a single brisk tempo throughout, Night of the Dark Horse is an energetic musical journey dedicated to the efforts of unlikely winners everywhere. Dur: 2:40

The logging industry of Rib Lake in northern Wisconsin faded away 70 years ago, but echoes of that era remain today. Echoes in the Woods depicts the large mechanized logging camps of that earlier time, and also the quiet beauty of the forests and lakes in the region today. Using an overture format and a sense of bold adventure, this work features exciting rhythmic passages contrasted with a flowing and lyrical middle

This entertaining medley of great show music combines Superstar Theme, Don't Cry For Me Argentina, King Herod's Song, and Memory into a moving and dramatic medley that you and your students will love!
titre: Andrew Lloyd Webber A Symphonic Portrait

description: Originally scored by the legendary Luther Henderson for full orchestra and brass quintet, here is a great-sounding adaptation for concert band by Paul Murtha that features three classic Ellington compositions. Includes: CottonTail, Sophisticated Lady and It Don't Mean a Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing).

Master arranger Luther Henderson created many of the signature arrangements performed by the Canadian Brass, including this classic. Paul Murtha has authentically adapted Luther's version for concert band with this well-craftedarrangement. (Grade 4)

Based on the quintet arrangements of the Canadian Brass from their CD/DVD “A Christmas Experiment”, here is a real holiday treat for concert band. In a style reminiscent of P.D.Q. Bach and Spike Jones, this masterfulsetting touches on an unlikely blend of musical styles and moods. This entertaining medley is sure to liven up any Winter concert!

In the spirit of Bugler's Holiday except cranked up a couple of notches, hold on to your hat for this spectacular trumpet trio feature with concert band. Written by Toronto trumpeter Johnny Cowell for the famed Canadian Brass, this dazzling showcase for mature trumpets emulates a ride on a high-powered roller coaster.

From the newest Canadian Brass album comes this one-of-a kind medley for concert band, featuring the unique artistry of the world's foremost brass quintet and the legendary songs of the Beatles. This fabulous collage includes: All You Need Is Love, Eleanor Rigby, With A Little Help From My Friends, When I'm Sixty Four, Michelle, and I Want To Hold Your Hand.

If your band enjoyed the popular 'Just A Closer Walk,' here's another Canadian Brass favorite, carefully scored for full band by Calvin Custer.  It begins with a slow 3/4 version, in a New Orleans 'street band' style, and then kicks into snazzy Dixieland, with small band features and roaring full band sections.  Another classic from the masters of showmanship.

W.C. Handy's swingin' blues is always a highlight of a Canadian Brass concert.  David Marshall's adaptation for band features ad lib solos (written out) and some 'downright dirty' dixieland for the entire band.  Great fun for all!

The simplicity and beauty of Pachelbel's haunting theme has made it one of the most famous classical compositions ever written, as evidenced by recording sales. Calvin Custer's adaptation keeps the integrity of the original Canadian Brass arrangement.

We are proud to present this edition in the Canadian Brass Concert Band Series.  Over the years, Bach's exquisite fugue has become an audience favorite of the Canadian Brass and is now available for concert band with this skillful transcription by Calvin Custer.  A wonderful addition for your library!
titre: Little Fugue (Little Fugue in G Minor)

description: From Berlioz's 'Symphonie Fantasique,' Calvin Custer has carefully captured the picturesque drama of the original orchestral work.  Opening with a solemn procession that quickly transforms into a brilliant march, the piece continues to build in intensity up to the final closing chords.  A dynamic transcription for intermediate bands.
Delightfully ghoulish, this arrangement of the classic TV theme is a great way to teach 6/8 time and have a lot of fun, too.  Don't forget your box of creepy sounding percussion instruments.

A spectacular medley with optional narration, featuring the best from Broadway's golden era (1934-1959).  Includes: Anything Goes (Anything Goes), It Ain't Necessarily So ( Porgy And Bess), It's Delovely (Red, Hot, and Blue), My Funny Valentine (Babes In Arms), Oklahoma! (Oklahoma!), How Are Things In Glocca Morra? (Finian's Rainbow), Another Op'nin', Another Show (Kiss Me Kate), Getting To Know You (The King And I),
titre: Broadway Journey: 25 Years Of Golden Classics

description: Inspired by the popular recording, A Canadian Brass Christmas, this medley features Ding Dong! Merrily On High, I Saw Three Ships, The Huron Carol, and Here We Come A-Wassailing. Adapted by the talented Canadian Brass arrangerHoward Cable.

Using nothing faster than a quarter note (except 8th notes in percussion) and working in melody spots for every section, Michael Oare does a masterful job of capturing a sense of adventure - and possibly danger! - in this powerful work for beginners. This is sure to become a favorite! Dur: 1:55
Lowden - Grade 4

We guaramtee that this is the best example of 'rock & roll' for young band that you'll find anywhere!  The tune, made famous by Bill Haley And The Comets says everything there is to say about early 'rock & roll' and this arrangement by Zane Van Auken is superb!

Veteran composer Eric Osterling has provided us with many great marches over the years and this energetic 2/4 march is one of his best. Solid ensemble writing, easy-to-teach stylistic features, and great audience appeal make this a wonderful addition for any band program. (2:00)
The disco rage of the '70s, The Village People, has caught on once again with today's kids.  Your students will love this new version of their biggest hit, arranged by Larry Norred.
Driving, eighth-note rock is what kids love to play and this one's a classic.  A bit of rock 'n' roll nostalgia from Little Eva.

Featuring a front line of trumpet, clarinet, trombone, and tuba, here's three classic Dixieland tunes combined in a superb showcase for developing groups.  Includes: Five Foot Two, Sweet Georgia Brown, and Charleston.
A bold, adventuresome overture for developing bands. Features an optional djembe drum in the percussion section.
An important song with a message from the DreamWorks film.
titre: When You Believe (from The Prince of Egypt)

description: Swing's the thing, now more than ever with this trademark tune from the Duke.
Touching ballad from Disney's Mulan.
In a medium swing style, a very easy version of one of the Duke's biggest songs.
Here's the tune to feature your ambitious players - a fabulous section feature.
A solid, well-written medley that includes O Come, All Ye Faithful - O Christmas Tree - and Joy To The World.
Grade 1 standard, including teaching aids and unison bass line. Helps players develop a swing style.
Andrew Lloyd Webber's timeless hit from Cats, now available in this very easy version.

Based on the distinctive and mesmerizing version recorded by Mannheim Steamroller, this authentic adaptation by Robert Longfield could be the hit of your holiday concert. Beautifully scored with creative harmonies and band vocals.
Nowak - Grade 3
Motown artists have recorded it and the California Raisins have danced to it.  The appeal of this great tune never gets old!
titre: I Heard It Through the Grapevine

description: Featured as the opening theme for the popular Drew Carey Show, this up-tempo arrangement really rocks...even if you're not from Cleveland.
Originally a hit in the 60's, this is one of those rare tunes popular with all ages.  Recently used in the hit movie, There's Something About Mary.
The Beatles landmark animated film has been released again, and a new generation is getting to know timeless hits like this one.

Ever have trouble identifying which Sousa march you're hearing?  Paul Murtha complicates it even more by rearranging several of Sousa's march fragments into a clever novelty that will lighten up any program.

From the classic movie about the Fab 4, Michael Sweeney has written a new easy medley that includes four of the mega-hits from this pop culture phenomena. Includes: A Hard Day's Night, And I Love Her, Can't Buy Me Love, and If I Fell.
titre: Selections from A Hard Day's Night

description: Here's a clever feature for the whole band that will add a little south of the border spice to your next concert. Catchy melodies and infectious rhythms make this one fun.

Discovery Plus - Grade 2 Ricky Martin's the hottest item on the airwaves these days and his latest single is a major cross-over hit. John Higgins captures the great hook and rhythmic Latin-pop groove in this easy-play version foryounger concert bands.

What a great idea!  Here's 11 of the biggest swing hits from two eras, the 40's and the 90's, cleverly put together in a medley that will turn your concert hall into a dance hall.  Eric's skilled writing makes it fun and easy to play for any group.  This one's an entertainment winner.  Includes: Woodchopper's Ball, Jumpin' Jack, Zoot Suit Riot, Puttin' On the Ritz, It Don't Mean a Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing),

This year your band can pay tribute to the great Duke Ellington on the 100th anniversary of his birth.  From his incredible legacy of American jazz songs, Michael Sweeney has selected three of Duke's best known tunes to form this new medley for concert band.  Includes: Satin Doll, Mood Indigo, and It Don't Mean a Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing).

Two perennial favorites make this clever medley a natural program choice for your Christmas season.  Jingle Bell Rock  and  Rockin' Around The Christmas Tree  are combined with an easy pop style, arranged by Paul Murtha.

A new version of this American favorite features distant trumpet calls, a fresh harmonization, and a bold, dramatic ending. Jay's arrangement is a winner for younger groups who need quality, multi-use arrangements in their library.
titre: The Battle Hymn of the Republic

description: With this year's 40th anniversary of Motown and its rich history of American popular music, here's a musical tribute that includes three classic hits: I Heard It Through The Grapevine (Marvin Gaye), My Girl (The Temptations), and ABC (The Jackson Five).

Here is a marvelous arrangement of the striking and sensitive ballad from the timeless Broadway musical and 2012 motion picture Les Miserables. Scored for younger players, John's setting is lush and mature sounding with limited technical demands.
Here's the exciting Spanish classic made popular by Stan Kenton.  This powerful arrangement will add flair and drama to any performance!

John Williams has once again been called upon to create inspirational and powerful music for the Olympics. Featured on his new CD American Journey in addition to the Winter Games in Utah, this impressive theme is handled here byyoung band expert Michael Sweeney. This excellent arrangement sounds much harder than it really is and will be an impressive addition to your next concert.

Nothing says rock and roll like this vintage song originally recorded by The Kingsmen. This up-tempo arrangement combines the familiar riffs of the original and includes a short trumpet solo or section feature. This one is a must!

description: Reading the title of this piece, namely “The Happy Village Smiths” it rather suggests a character piece than a zestful march. However, the saying “Don’t let yourself be fooled” also applies in this instance, as “The Happy Village Smiths” belong to Fuc k’s most popular marches. In an article that appeared in a Styrian local paper in the 1930s, Christine Fuc k speaks about common vacations with her husband in

titre: Arietta Voi che sapete (aus Figaros Hochzeit)

description: Written for band. Arranged by J. Trayter.
Version for Wind Band. Legendary work composed for the 1956 Hoffnung Festival featuring solo passages for Vacuum Cleaners, a Floor-Polisher and Rifles.

titre: The Legend of the Amber Room

sous_titre: Solo for Alto Saxophone and band

titre: The Flight of the Bumble Bee

sous_titre: It Ain'T Necessarily So/I Got Plenty Of Nuttin'

Concerto for Bass Clarinet and Band
In The Mystic Land Of Egypt

instrumentation: Concert Band, Trumpet and Alto Saxophone

titre: Give us Pease / The Happy Cyclist

sous_titre: For Euphonium or Trombone and Band

description: Let Freedom Ring is a stirring fantasy on My Country 'Tis of Thee’. Weaving familiar strains of the song into the midst of brass fanfares and woodwind flourishes, composer Ryan Nowlin creates a moving patriotic portrait of the U.S.A., its founders, and its women and men in uniform.

Les Aventures de Pinocchio , de l’écrivain italien, Carlo Collodi, est un classique de la littérature pour enfants et de la littérature italienne du XIXe siècle. Célèbre dans le monde entier, ce conte moderne a fait l’objet de multiples adaptations. Le compositeur espagnol, Ferrer Ferran, l’a mis en musique. Sa suite symphonique en quatre mouvements ( Pinocchio, Geppetto et le Grillon-qui-parle • La fée Turquoise •

La Sagrada Familia  (Le Temple de la Sainte Famille) est l’œuvre emblématique de l’architecte catalan. Elle est l’un des chantiers majeurs en cours de réalisation dans le monde aujourd’hui. Cet édifice monumental est tellement identifié Gaud , que l’on oublie souvent qu’il n’est ni l’initiateur du projet, ni le réalisateur de la plupart des parties visibles du b timent actuel.La première pierre fut posée en 1882

Fils d’un modeste chaudronnier, Antoni Gaud i Cornet naît Reus dans la province de Tarragone, le 25 juin 1852. Souffrant de rhumatismes articulaires particulièrement invalidants, Gaud fut contraint de longues périodes de repos dès son plus jeune ge. Il passait des heures observer la nature. Gaud a octroyé un nouveau langage artistique l’architecture. Son style unique se caractérise par des lignes souples et des

Monstre fabuleux, le dragon est présent dans les légendes de la quasi-totalité des cultures et demeure l’objet d’une fascination intemporelle. Animal maléfique et destructeur pour les Occidentaux ; messager des dieux pour les Orientaux, il est le maître des éléments et symbolise la puissance des forces de la nature. Entrez dans l’univers sombre et mystérieux du Dragon rouge.

Taillés dans une falaise de grès rose sur la rive occidentale du Nil, les deux temples d’Abou Simbel ont été b tis sur ordre du pharaon Ramsès II. Associant le culte de sa personne celui des divinités R , Amon et Ptah, Ramsès assurait sa gloire. Le grand temple d’Abou Simbel est l’un des mieux conservés d’Égypte. Dans le sanctuaire, au fond de l’édifice, se dressent quatre statues taillées dans le roc. Ramsès II

Construite par les Romains au IIe siècle après Jésus-Christ au large de la ville de La Corogne en Espagne, la Tour d’Hercule est le plus ancien et l’unique phare antique du monde encore en activité. Depuis des siècles, sa construction apparaît au centre de nombreuses légendes locales. Parmi ces légendes, il en est une qui raconte que le géant et puissant roi de Brigantia (Brigantium), Gérion, obligeait ses sujets lui

El meu iaio  (“Mon grand-père”) est une passacaille pleine d’allant et de charme. Avec des accents typiquement espagnols et des couleurs vives, la musique se révèle attrayante, captivante et délicieusement agréable.Octavi Ruiz est un homme passionné de musique, un promoteur de la culture, de l’enseignement et de l’éducation musicale : un b tisseur, un prophète en son pays. Octavi Ruiz est le directeur musical de la

Depuis 1989, année de son ouverture, l’Institut d'artmoderne de Valence en Espagne (Instituto Valenciano de Arte Moderno ou IVAM) s'impose comme une référence dans les domaines de la recherche et de la promotion de l’art du XXe siècle IVAM, de Ferrer Ferran, s’inspire de la philosophie de cet art même, qui a fait de l’édifi ce qui l’abrite, un emblème de la culture du XXe siècle. La musique est une promenade

Ferrer Ferran a composé ce paso-doble fougueux l’occasion du 10e anniversaire du magasin d’instruments de musique Consolat de Mar Benaguasil, près de Valence en Espagne. Consolat de Mar est idéal pour ouvrir un concert. L’entrée et le passage final refl ètent la fierté inhérente au caractère espagnol. Le trio développe une mélodie fluide et expressive qui off re un charmant contraste avec la puissance solennelle de

La Escala Sido  fait partie d’une série de petits poèmes musicaux que Ferrer Ferran a composés l’intention des petits et grands musiciens en herbe, avec un objectif précis : égayer et valoriser les débuts, quelquefois difficiles, dans le monde fascinant de la musique.  La Escala Sido  s’appuie sur la totalité des sept notes de la gamme.

Ceremonial  est un triptyque composé pour l’inauguration de l’Auditorium Florida, lieu de résidence de l’Orchestre d’Harmonie Primitiva de Paiporta en Espagne. / L'introduction est écrite sous la forme d’une fanfare solennelle qui annonce l’ouverture de la cérémonie d’inauguration. Le second mouvement -  Marche  - s’ouvre avec une marche qui mène le passage vers l’exposition d’une mélodie élégante et expressive, en

Algemiz  est un arrangement de la composition originale  Aljama  pour dulzaina et Orchestre d’Harmonie, récompensée, en 1999, du Deuxième Prix du Concours de Composition pour dulzaina et orchestre de la ville d’Algemes en Espagne. La dulzaina est un instrument traditionnel anche double.Algemes (de l’arabe  algemiz , “village”), est une ville située sur les rives du fleuve Sucron, au sud de Valence. Le thème principal

El Bosque Mágico (La forêt magique)  a été donné en création mondiale, le 17 février 2002, au Palais de la Musique de Valence en Espagne par l’Orchestre d’Harmonie Municipal de Valence (Dir. : Pablo Sánchez Torella) et Jesús Fuster, hautbois solo. /  1. Acclaimed French composer Albert Roussel is known today for his famous pupils, Erik Satie and Edgard Varèse, as well as for his own marvelous works. Composed specifically for the famed Goldman Band and premiered in 1933 in New York City, A Glorious Day is an invigorating work written in a modified overture format of fast-slow-fast. Mark Fonder's critical edition provides a rare opportunity to play a pre-WWII original

Written in a grand film scoring style,  Rossano Galante's  Journey to the Lion's Castle  takes the listener on an exciting musical excursion of various moods and styles. The impressive opening strainsfeature woodwind flourishes and powerful brass lines. A graceful and majestic middle section offers a change of pace before the ending segment drives to a breathtaking finish. For mature bands, this could become a

Magnificent work from Karel Husa written in honor of Bedrich Smetana.  Demanding for all sections, the work begins quietly and quickly builds to open a concert with intensity and grandeur. Grades 4-5.

From Samuel Barber's acclaimed  First Symphony , here is a masterful adaptation for band of the stunningly beautiful lyric movement. While carefully preserving Barber's original intent, Richard has created a settingthat effectively suits the band medium.
sous_titre: Standard US Set (without European suppl. set)

description: Taken from Ellington's renowned suite  Black, Brown and Beige,  the song  Come Sunday  has become an acknowledged standard in its own right. With lush scoring and beautiful harmonies, here is a marvellousadaptation of this moving ballad featuring a solo Alto Sax with Concert Band. (Grade 4)
sous_titre: Standard US Set (without european suppl. parts)

description: Renowned film composer Danny Elfman entered the symphonic world with a flourish with his orchestral work  Serenada Schizophrana . Commissioned by the American Composers Orchestra in New York, it was premiered atCarnegie Hall in 2005. The third movement,  A Brass Thing , features an eclectic blend of styles and striking sonorities and is skillfully adapted for wind band by Richard Saucedo. Duration 5:30. (Grade 4)

Here is a bold and adventurous overture that works great as a concert opener. Reminiscent of an epic film score, this original composition features dynamic brass fanfares, sweeping woodwind lines and a wealth of stylistic andemotional variety. Impressive writing for mature groups. (Grade 4) (4:25)
Canadian Brass. For Double Brass Quintet.
Canadian Brass. For Double Brass Quintet.
Transcribed by Donald Hunsberger, this setting has been scored for the expanded orchestra wind section. Grade 4-5.
sous_titre: Standard US Set (without european suppl. parts)
titre: Passacaglia and Fugue in C Minor

description: Arranged by Frank Erickson. This exceptional work holds a special place in concert band literature (grades 4-5). In a bright 6/8 tempo throughout, the wonderful vitality of Grainger's writing makes for a truly memorable musical experience.
titre: Children's March (Over the Hills and Far Away)

description: Grade 4-5.
Score and Parts for Percy Grainger's  Lincolnshire Posy . For Concert Band Grades 4-5
Grades 4-5
titre: Ye Banks and Braes o' Bonnie Doon

description: Grades 4-5
sous_titre: Standard US Set (without european suppl. parts)

description: For Brass Band of Old Instruments (or modern brass quintet or sextet) and Concert Band. Arranged by Keith Brion. Grades 4-5.

This impressive and historically significant work is found on state lists all across the country and is highly respected as an important contribution to the contemporary literature for concert band. Composed in 1968 and memorializing the 1968 Soviet bloc invasion of Czechoslovakia, Husa arranged this for orchestra soon after. One year later Husa was awarded the Pulitzer Prize for his String Quartet No. 3.
Arranged for Concert Band by W. Herbert.

You can't lose when you get your administrators or other staff members involved in your performance. Teachers from Outer Space is a hilarious comedy skit for band that lets three or more of your staff members temporarily become outer space aliens and use every corny outer space joke in the book! If you are looking for a funny contrast highlight - greetings Earthling, you've found it!

This nice processional style piece will work in the concert and contest venue as well as at the graduation or awards ceremony. The stately tempo and rich scoring help your young musicians to sound their best. Carefully controlledranges and rhythms mean the piece can be prepared with limited rehearsal time.

This nice easy overture-style festival or concert piece will show off your band at its best. The exciting primary theme is contrasted with an engaging slow section and there are plenty of musical concepts to teach which are righton target for musicians at this level. Consider opening your next concert with Challenger Point. Dur: 3:05

James Curnow skillfully brings one of Tchaikovsky's most memorable symphonic themes to the concert band stage with this new arrangement. It's always a good idea to let your band members become familiar with great orchestrathemes. Whether used as a concert centerpiece or an exciting finale you'll want to have this mainstay of Romantic era music in your library. Dur: 4:45

Your young players will enjoy the mystery and grandeur of this descriptive piece about the isolated 12th-century Norman keep. Once a strong fortress, it is now little more than some stone walls and bits of rooms. What history has been made here? The colorful percussion and rich harmonies are expressive and intriguing. There's something for everyone in this stately original. Majestic!

James Curnow's clever arrangement of Jingle Bells masterfully keeps the range and rhythm demands at a pre-grade 1 level while assuring that all the players have fun in the preparation and performance. Every section is fullyinvolved, and the low woodwinds and brass get a little special time all their own. Great step dynamics are the perfect opportunity to make sure your players show a significant difference at each

This joyous arrangement is a great opener for your winter concert. Three well-known bell carols unite to make a sparkling and memorable treat - and what a great teaching tool for the concept of bell-tones that appear in numerousplaces. Brisk and engaging with lots of built-in contrasts, it's a sure winner.

What a great energetic way to open your Christmas concert and bring focus to the joyful sounds of the season! Themes from Spain, Czechoslovakia, Poland, England and France lead us on a delightful Christmas tour, and James Curnow'soutstanding orchestration technique ensures that all the musicians have rewarding parts to play. You'll enjoy the melodic twists and turns as the consistent unifying tempo charges implacably

This little gem will win over your audience from the very start. What a clever and well-crafted way to open your next winter concert! Sounding more advanced than it plays, this very accessible arrangement is a great choice for thewinter concert. Sparkling colors and creative melodic excursions make rehearsals as much fun as the performance. (Grade 1-1/2)

A refreshing and energetic treatment of one of the all-time best loved carols, Angels We Have Heard on High. Young musicians will love rehearsing and performing this stylistically creative little gem. The captivating developmentof the middle section of the piece and lots of contrasting instrumentation throughout makes this arrangement a wonderful experience for all. (Grade 1)

You've heard of the legendary Tyrannosaurus Rex. Well, this Tyrannosaurus ROCKS! Another fun one for Beginning Band by Mike Hannickel, it's as easy as can be but the kids will love it. If you have an old sousaphone and a baritonesax mouthpiece you can make a mighty Tyrann-o-Phone for the optional solo at the end of the piece. (Grade 1/2)

Mariah Carey made a huge addition to our holiday listening experience with her Merry Christmas album. This arrangement includes three of those tunes woven into a medley by Joe Murphy: All I Want for Christmas Is You · Miss You Most (At Christmas Time) · Christmas (Baby Please Come Home).

titre: Go Tell it on the Mountain

description: This lush and richly scored arrangement by Larry Kerchner will be especially rewarding for younger bands. The melody of It Came Upon a Midnight Clear is beautifully intermingled with Dona Nobis Pacem in this lovely setting.
titre: It Came Upon a Midnight Clear

description: The two melodies we know as Away in a Manger are lovingly intertwined - yet another Tom Wallace masterpiece.
This ingenious and appealing arrangement by Jeff Simmons merges The First Noel and Pachelbel's Canon in D.

Composed in the style of a military quickstep, Pas Redoublé is a concert march reminiscent of the gallops by Offenbach and other 19 century composers. Transcribed for band by Arthur Frackenpohl in 1972, this work has retained a prominent position in the wind band literature. Dur: 3:20 (Grade 4)

This gem from 1985 has steadily become one of the classic repertoire pieces for young bands. Even though it is heavily cross-cued making it suitable for smaller bands, this beautiful work is rich in melodic content, variedscoring, and marvelous counterlines and harmonies. An effective performance vehicle that also teaches legato style and musical sensitivity. Dur: 4:00 (Grade 3)

The Dylan Thomas poem Do Not Go Gentle into That Good Night was the motivation for this musical composition. While not a programmatic depiction of the poem, the work attempts to recreate the essence of the poem in sound. Theopening motive, representative of the life force, permeates much of the work. The use of sound layers - in the form of polytonal hymns - calls to mind the struggles and persistence of the human
titre: Do Not Go Gentle Into That Good Night

description: For that first holiday concert, here is a wonderful and very easy setting of O Come Emmanuel in an expressive style.
A Puerto Rican folk carol is the basis for this clever holiday feature that has plenty of Latin percussion and performance options.

Paul Jennings as created an outstanding setting for this familiar canon for beginning groups. Starting softly with the woodwinds, the piece builds gradually throughout giving every section a chance to play this marvelous melody.
Tchaikovsky's most frequently performed work is now available in a highly simplified version for young players. An impressive concert finale!
This Spanish-style concert march is carefully designed for beginning players. Strong melodies and careful part writing make this a winner for your first and second year players.

A ghoulish and sinister concoction that will delight any audience, particularly on a dark, dreary Friday night concert.  Jay's medley includes several musical nightmares that your players will love to play: Tales From The Crypt, Psycho, Jaws, and several other unnerving moments.
titre: Things That Go Bump In The Night

description: By interweaving fragments of several holiday favorites into a brilliant fanfare, James Curnow has crafted this spirited, festive work. A perfect opener for your next Christmas program.
The majesty and drama of this classic band piece has been carefully scored so that all parts are accessible to younger players.

From James Curnow's acclaimed series of orchestral masterwork editions for young band.  Includes four of the best known movements: The Sea and Sinbad's Ships, The Story Of The Kalendar Prince, The Young Prince And The Young Princess, and The Festival At Bagdad.
Curnow - Grade 3

This is the authentic version recorded by Whitney Houston and first performed at Super Bowl XXV during the Gulf War. Gifted arranger John Clayton has adapted the orchestral version he did for Whitney into this exhilarating arrangement for concert band. (Also available are compatible SATB, SAB and 2-Part choral voicings.)

This may well be one of the finest transcriptions ever done for developing bands.  Jim Curnow's carefully crafted arrangement features the six most loved movements of Moussorgsky's best-known work in settings that capture all the life and color of the original orchestral versions.  It includes: Promenade, The Old Castle, The Ox Cart, Ballet Of The Unhatched Chicks, Hut Of Baba Yaga, The Great Gate Of Kiev.
A jubilant way to open any holiday concert.
titre: Fanfare on Joy to the World

description: Already a classic of the Broadway/London stage, this Andrew Lloyd Webber theme is rich with dramatic appeal.  Easy and solidly scored by Jay Bocook.
titre: The Phantom of the Opera (Main Theme)

description: Here is a superb symphonic treatment of the best-known movements from Tchaikovsky's ballet. Not only does Jim Curnow capture the spirit of the orchestral version, but he has transformed the work into a setting that lets the modernconcert band sound its best.

This perennial favorite is a great way to feature one or more of your mallet percussionists.  The wind parts are extremely playable, and you will find that this piece works well at a variety of tempos.
Claude Smith has fashioned a brilliant, rhapsodic setting of this stirring carol. Christmas programming at its finest!

The popular Christmas classic  White Christmas  has been beautifully arranged for concert (wind) band by John Edmondson. This is easy enough to be played by High School bands, and yet full-sounding enough for more advanced bands.

Three of the Beatles' favourite hits are combined in this easy-to-play medley for developing groups. Eric Osterling's approach to young band writing ensures success for young players. Includes: Eleanor Rigby, Yesterday, and A Hard Day's Night.
sous_titre: Eleanor Rigby - Yesterday - A Hard Day's Night

description: 'Life Goes On'...the appropriate theme from an important TV drama, in an easy-play version.  A Beatles classic with a memorable hook and a great message.

We're pleased to release this vigorous and venturesome new piece from our foremost composer of mature wind band literature.  After a brilliant fanfare opening, the main theme is woven through variations in three large contrasting sections, with the fanfare returning to culminate this impressive and substantial work.  A superb new publication for serious bands.

We are proud to publish Alfred Reed's Third Symphony.  From the intensity of the opening meovement to the exquisite counterpoint of the finale, Dr. Reed draws the most from the resources of the contemporary concert band.  Written for the U.S. Air Force Band, this powerful three-movement work is certain to be a lasting contribution to the world of band literature.

Here's one of the most spectacular program number ever written!  Only the talents of Warren Barker could produce this rhapsodic medley of Sousa's favorite marches, ending with a version of The Stars And Stripes Forever that's sure to bring down the house.

Commissioned by the National Honorary Band Fraternity and Sorority of Kappa Kappa Psi, this brilliant work is exemplary of Claude T. Smith's consummate mastery of the concert band medium.  The four definitive movements reflect his rhythmic inventiveness, melodic exuberance and disinctive harmonic sense.

Here's a brilliant concert work from the master of the contemporary British band style.  Brassy and full of contrast, it maintains a forceful rhythmic vitality throughout.  A sensational addition to the repertoire.
Considered to be Van Morrison's signature hit, this was first recorded in the '60s but remains popular today. The rhythmic and upbeat feel of this solid arrangement will liven up any concert.

From the group Train, this popular hit has stayed on the charts for more than a year and is on track to becoming a pop classic. This great-sounding arrangement includes plenty of variety in scoring and textures while being easy tolearn and fun to perform.

Recorded by Coldplay, this enduring hit from 2003 represents some of the best elements of contemporary pop music - a catchy melody, well-constructed counterlines and harmonies, and an infectious groove. This arrangement by James Kazik effectively captures these elements from the original.

From the dramatic finale to the third film in the popular Twilight Saga movie series, here is Howard Shore's distinctive and memorable main theme. Robert Longfield's arrangement is carefully scored so that all sections (even lowbrass) get a chance to play the haunting theme.

Taking a similar approach to his popular Celtic Air and Dance, Michael Sweeney creatively combines two 17th-century carols (Bring a Torch, Jeanette, Isabella and Fum, Fum, Fum) into this attractive and distinctive setting for theholidays.

This famous duet from the 1940s has been recorded by countless artists over the years, and was featured in the hit movie Elf starring Will Ferrell. Here is a terrific-sounding arrangement for young players.

Cette ballade d’une beauté envo tante fut enregistrée pour la première fois par Cyndi Lauper en 1986. Elle reste toujours populaire et peut être retrouvée dans le nouveau film animé succès  Les Trolls . Un changement de tempo magnifique, parfait pour des bands.

Here is the perfect choice for an entertaining and unique holiday selection. Johnnie Vinson combines a light swing treatment of Jingle-Bell Rock, a lush version of Frosty the Snow Man, and a jazzy Here Comes Santa Claus into a terrific medley for young bands. Sure to be an audience pleaser!

Revived for the earthquake relief efforts in Haiti, We Are the World is still a powerful and moving anthem of hope and unity. Here is an arrangement for young bands that will go together quickly and sound great.

The Fab Four exploded on the American music scene with a banner year of hits in 1964. This medley of Beatle favorites includes I Want to Hold Your Hand, And I Love Her and Twist and Shout. It was a good year!
sous_titre: I Want to Hold Your Hand - And I Love Her - Twist and Shout

description: Taking the musical phrase dashing through the snow and weaving it around original material, John Moss has created a wonderful work for band that captures the flavor and joy of the holiday season.

Booker T. & the MG's recorded this iconic instrumental hit in the early '60s, and it continues to be popular in film and TV decades later. Instantly recognizable, this is sure to be a hit with all audiences.

Picking up right where the popularity of the first High School Musical left off, the second movie offers more catchy tunes and energetic rhythms. Here is a solidly scored medley including What Time Is It, You Are the Music in Me,and All for One. Dur: 4:00

After 18 seasons of unparalleled success on television, Homer and all the gang have finally made it to the big screen! Here is a dynamite arrangement of one of the most unique and recognizable theme songs ever!

With select new themes from the blockbuster third Pirates movie along with a hint of the familiar earlier melodies, this very playable version for younger bands is sure to be a hit with audiences and students alike!

How many times have you wondered what to do with all those bell players? Here's a great solution in this clever holiday arrangement featuring 2-part mallet percussion (bells or vibes). Including “ Joy to the World ” and “ Angels We Have Heard on High ”, these players finally get the spotlight they deserve!
Christina Aguilera's big hit is rhythmic and dynamic. With hot ensemble riffs and dynamic percussion parts, this is certain to add some excitement to your next concert.

With the reality TV show You're the One That I Want leading up to the Broadway revival, the ever popular musical Grease is enjoying renewed interest. Here's one of the big hits from the show in an arrangement playable by beginninggroups.
Filled with rock energy and rhythmic drive, here is an easy arrangement of this hit song from Disney's High School Musical. Your percussion section will have fun with this one! Dur: 2:00

Using a beloved carol as a point of departure, John has crafted a marvelous piece for holiday concerts. Sensitive and lyrical in nature, it also features nice emotional pacing and superb scoring for young bands. Dur: 2:40
titre: A Shepherd's Carol (based on The First Noel)

description: John Moss has taken this familiar holiday melody and crafted an up-tempo and lively setting all in 4/4 (rather than 6/8). This unique version is sure to be a welcome addition to your band's holiday offerings. Carefully scored togive every section interesting parts. Dur: 2:15
Featuring the mega hits Thriller, Somewhere Out There, and Footloose, here is a hard-hitting medley for young players that is sure to be enjoyed by all. The '80s never sounded so good!

Combining the familiar Canon in D with a multitude of popular Christmas carols, this clever and unique arrangement for beginning bands will be the talk of the concert. See how many tunes you can identify. includes:  Canon In D; The First Noel; Go, Tell It On The Mountain; Good King Wenceslas; Hark! The Herald Angels Sing; Jingle Bells; Jolly Old St. Nicholas; Joy To The World; Up On The Housetop; We Wish You A Merry
From a hit in the '60s by Johnny Rivers to frequent use in contemporary movies, this is everyone's favorite spy theme in an easy version.

Ray Charles' genius is evident in the wide variety of songs he recorded and made his own. Johnnie's solidly scored medley for young players includes such Ray Charles classics as: Georgia on My Mind, What'd I Say and Hallelujah ILove Her So.

One of the all-time favorite production numbers for the Canadian Brass is this clever arrangement that combines The Hallelujah Chorus with When the Saints Go Marching In. Johnnie has created an easier version of this classicallowing it to be performed by younger groups. What a great idea! (Grade 21/2)

This magnificent march was actually composed by Eric Osterling in 1979. In this new edition, Eric has kept the chromatic flare and distinctive style but adapted it to the needs of younger players. Now even small and inexperienced bands can enjoy this march classic!

The 1960s were a golden time for rock and roll, and many of the hits came from across the ocean. Here is a fun collection of British imports including Downtown (Petula Clark), Ferry 'Cross the Mersey (Gerry & The Pacemakers) and IWant to Hold Your Hand (The Beatles).

Herb Alpert and the Tijuana Brass made this a huge hit in the 1960s, and now your trumpets can be the hit of the concert with this easy version. Bring the festive atmosphere of a bull fight to your next concert (without the bull).

Written in a two-beat style and in a minor key, this is a fun little ragtime number that will be a nice change of pace on any concert. The clarinets get some noodling time in their low register and there are some nice full ensemble passages as well.
From Kermit the Frog's lily pad to your concert stage, this easy setting of the Muppets' best-known ballad is sure to be a favorite with audiences and students alike. Nicely scored for young bands.
From the motion picture We Were Soldiers and featured during the Ronald Reagan memorial service in Washington, D.C., this beautiful hymn is presented in an easy and moving setting.
titre: The Mansions of the Lord (from We Were Soldiers)

description: Johnnie Vinson presents three holiday favorites all treated in an easy-flowing swing style in this very attractive medley for young players. Here's a great way to teach swing in a unique sounding arrangement for Christmas. Includes  Deck the Hall ,  Jingle Bells  and the Irving Berlin classic  White Christmas .

Introduce your young players to the music of Duke Ellington with this easy arrangement of one of the Duke's classics. Written in a medium slow swing style, this one will make your band sound great and is sure to be a hit with theparents.
The distinctive music of Charlie Brown and the Peanuts gang comes alive in this enjoyable arrangement by Paul Murtha. Fun for all audiences!

Opening with the slow style of a New Orleans funeral march (with an optional combo), the arrangement then shifts gears to an uptempo Dixieland celebration. Marvelous and effective writing for younger players.
titre: Just a Closer walk With Thee

description: Discovery Series - Grade 1.5 This unforgettable theme from the original Spider-Man television series was brought back for the recent blockbuster movie. With a catchy melody and a driving rock feel, this is a guaranteed favorite with students and audiences alike.

The distinctive harmonies and sounds of the Renaissance period are used in a wonderfully effective setting by Johnnie Vinson. Including Carol of the Birds, Veni Emmanuel and In Dulci Jubilo, this festive and unique arrangement also inlcudes optional recorder parts.

Some of the early classic TV cartoon shows generated the most memorable themes. Paul's fast paced and well-written arrangement includes I'm Popeye the Sailor Man, Casper the Friendly Ghost and The Mighty Mouse Theme (Here I Come to Save the Day). This is sure to be an audience favorite!

From the popular musical Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat here is an exciting yet easy version of the main song. The introduction starts quietly in 3/4 before launching into a driving rock style. This excellent arrangement features solid scoring that will sound great with beginning players.
sous_titre: From Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat

description: After years of writing clever and memorable tunes for the movies (Toy Story and A Bug's Life to name a few) Randy Newman finally won a much deserved Grammy for this song from the hit movie Monsters, Inc. Michael Brown has skillfully arranged it for young players in a medium 2-beat swing style.
titre: If I Didn't Have You (from Monsters, Inc.)

description: Here is the distinctive Duke Ellington classic in a very easy setting for band. By using a moderately fast tempo in 4/4 Michael was able to capture the feel of the original using nothing faster than a quarter note in the wind parts. The percussion are featured briefly and compliment the style of the arrangement very nicely.
This popular song from The Sound of Music can serve as a nice change of pace for a holiday concert or a program selection for any occasion. Well-scored with easy rhythms.
titre: My Favorite Things (from The Sound of Music)

description: The Beatles-classic arranged for brass section.

It's hard to find a musical that has wider appeal and more captivating music than Meredith Willson's The Music Man. Johnnie's medley for younger groups features The Wells Fargo Wagon, Till There Was You, and Seventy Six Trombones.
This stunning feature movie from the Walt Disney studios features a wealth of musical styles from quiet sensitive moments to fierce, dramatic excitement.
Here is a fresh sounding holiday setting of traditional French carols. Includes: Christmas Comes Anew; Bring a Torch, Jeanette, Isabella; and Pat-a-Pan.
Johnnie's effective arrangement uses layering of melodies and plenty of percussion to bring something a little different for holiday programming.
Too often the low brass section gets ignored when it comes to playing the melody. John Moss has remedied the situation with this great arrangement of this holiday favorite.

From the highly acclaimed Steven Spielberg film, this emotional hymn by John Williams evokes a feeling of hope and strength amid the overall tone of reverence. This arrangement is beautifully scored for young groups while maintaining the integrety of the original. Exposed sections featuring woodwinds or brass are cross cued for bands with incomplete instrumentation.
titre: Hymn to the Fallen (from Saving Private Ryan)

description: From Disney and Pixar's hit Toy Story 2, here is an easy version of the beautiful featured ballad sung in the film by Sarah McLachlan.
This is the sultry hit song from the newest James Bond movie, recorded by the group Garbage.
From Big Bad Voodoo Daddy's newest CD, this is a medium tempo boogie-woogie that really swings.  Guaranteed fun.

Those madcap characters from TV's past have made a whole new audience, thanks to the Nickelodeon cable channel. Four of their biggest hits are combined in a fun-loving medley for developing bands. Includes: Daydream Believer, Last Train To Clarksville, I'm A Believer, and Hey, Hey We're The Monkees.

titre: The King Of Rock N' Roll

description: This very easy setting of John Williams' dramatic work is designed to help beginning bands sound full, even with incomplete instrumentation.
How about a hit TV theme that's not only a march, but also features trumpets and drums!  This music writes itself for young concert band.  Your kids will love it!
sous_titre: from the Paramount Television Series JAG

description: There's no better way to open or close a pops concert than with this Irving Berlin classic.  John Moss has given it a face lift with his new edition that teaches your young players that 'show-biz'style.
titre: There's No Business Like Show Business

description: This year it's the only way to celebrate the holiday - with zoot suits and mistletoe!

Perfect for light holiday occasions, here is a terrific and entertaining medley for band and chorus, or for band alone. Includes: Frosty the Snow Man; Jingle-Bell Rock; Let It Snow!; Rudolph the Red Nosed Reindeer and Silver Bells. Also Available: 08740139/$2.50 SATB · 08740140/$2.50 3-Part Mixed · 08740141/$2.50 2-Part · 04626014/$40.00 Opt. String Pak Corresponding Choral Octavos available  here .
sous_titre: A Christmas Medley for Concert Band with optional Chorus and Strings

description: Need a lighter, yet well-scored change of pace? Michael Sweeney has styled this Latin flavored composition that fits right in the pocket for young bands. It features plenty of percussion to keep your players busy along with appealing Latin rhythms for the entire ensemble. Dur: 3:45
The only thing missing from this is the lyrics (and the hoof prints), but the music will leave your audiences with a grin. A great novelty for a developing band's winter program.
titre: Grandma Got Run Over by a Reindeer

description: This powerful work for beginning players is written entirely in one tempo in the style of an extended fanfare. Appropriate for use at contests or festivals, this will make your band sound great with limited rehearsal time. (Includes full performance CD)
A fun rock groove that features those who will have complete world power in the near future - your percussion section.
titre: When Drummers Take Over The World

description: The simple, memorable theme from the hit movie is an ideal concert piece for band.  Arranger Johnnie Vinson has written an outstanding version that your younger groups can play with confidence.

titre: Can You Feel The Love Tonight

description: MusicWorks - Grade 1 Rarely does any single publication have such an effect on band literature as this unique and striking composition from 1994. Individually, the parts are relatively simple. Yet the combined effect is sophisticated and impressive far beyond its easy level. Michael uses a wealth of contemporary devices (including tone clusters, recorders, singing, pencil tapping) to create an aura of prehistoric
An infectious funky groove that is sure to be a hit with your players.  Starts with a gospel-style chorale and is pure fun for all.

Written in one tempo, this outstanding piece contrasts timbres and dynamics between the brass, woodwinds, and percussion.  The themes are rhythmic and the percussion writing is creative and interesting.  Another winner from Michael Sweeney.

This landmark work for beginning groups helped to set the standard for music at this level. Boldly written to include dissonances, varied scoring effects, and driving rhythmic ostinatos, Michael Sweeney's classic is dramatic andmature sounding beyond its easy level. This new edition includes full performance CD recording. (2:30)
Concert Band arrangement that will get them all singing and dancing in the aisles!
titre: Santa Claus is Comin' to Town

description: From the recent Canadian Brass recording Stars & Stripes comes this impressive setting of one of the most popular folk tunes to come out of the Civil War era. Trumpeter Brandon Ridenour found new and inventive ways to treat thistimeless melody, and Michael Brown has effectively adapted it for full concert band. Commemorate the 150th anniversary of this important time in America's history with this terrific setting.

Legendary composer, arranger, and author Rayburn Wright is responsible for initiating the storied jazz program at the Eastman School of Music, and was also a composer for film and television. His masterful setting of Shakermelodies includes the familiar Simple Gifts, along with The Happy Journey and I've Set My Face for Zion's Kingdom. Used to feature a separate brass quintet or with members within an ensemble's
sous_titre: for Brass Quintet and Concert Band

description: One of the  best-loved Christmas songs of all time. You'll play Michael's easy, yet rich-sounding, setting at holiday concerts year after year.
sous_titre: Chestnuts Roasting on an Open Fire
